# Next.js 16 + React 19 — Suspiros de Papel

## Version Check

This repo runs Next.js 16 (App Router). Before writing Next.js-specific code:

```bash
cat node_modules/next/package.json | grep '"version"'
```

APIs differ from training data. Treat older knowledge as potentially stale.

## App Router Rules

```
app/page.tsx        → imports sections ONLY. No business logic.
app/layout.tsx      → fonts, metadata, global providers
app/globals.css     → CSS vars, Tailwind base, design tokens
```

No `getServerSideProps` or `getStaticProps` — those are Pages Router. Use async Server Components.

## Server vs Client Components

```tsx
// Default: Server Component (no directive needed)
// "use client" ONLY when you need: useState, useEffect, browser APIs, event handlers

// ❌ Wrong: making layout components client-side
"use client"
export function HeroSection() {  // just renders HTML, no interactivity
  return <section>...</section>
}

// ✅ Right: Server Component by default
export function HeroSection() {
  return <section>...</section>
}
```

## Eliminating Waterfalls (CRITICAL)

```tsx
// ❌ Sequential (waterfall)
const a = await fetchA()
const b = await fetchB()  // waits for A

// ✅ Parallel
const [a, b] = await Promise.all([fetchA(), fetchB()])
```

## Image Optimization

```tsx
import Image from "next/image"

// ✅ Always explicit dimensions + WebP + priority on LCP
<Image
  src="/images/portfolio/item.webp"
  alt="Descripción del producto"
  width={600}
  height={400}
  priority  // on LCP image only
  className="object-cover"
/>
```

## TypeScript

```tsx
// No `any` — use generics or `unknown`
// Props interfaces above component, not inline
interface SectionProps {
  heading?: string
}
export function Section({ heading = "Default" }: SectionProps) { ... }
```

## Metadata (Phase 1 launch task)

```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "Suspiros de Papel — Regalos personalizados en Zihuatanejo",
  description: "...",
  openGraph: { ... }
}
```

## Bundle Rules

- No default exports (prevents tree-shaking issues)
- No framer-motion (not installed, use `useScrollReveal`)
- No lodash/moment — use native JS
- Analyze with `pnpm build` → check output sizes

## Code Quality

- Components ≤ 150 lines — split if longer
- No `console.log` in commits
- `pnpm lint && pnpm build` must pass before commit
